# Adapt Agency — website design rules

Source: internal design brief (website-design-rules). Applies to all frontend and static-site work in this repository.

## Always do first

- Apply the **frontend-design** Cursor skill before writing any frontend code, every session, without exception.
- Check **`brand_assets/`** before designing anything. Use whatever is there — logos, palettes, style guides. Do not invent brand elements if real ones exist.

## Project types

This project may be one of the following — confirm with the user if unclear:

| Mode | Approach |
|------|----------|
| **Single `index.html`** | All styles inline; Tailwind via CDN |
| **Multi-page HTML/CSS** | Shared styles, logical file structure |
| **Next.js / React** | Components; Tailwind via PostCSS |

**Default:** single `index.html` unless the user specifies otherwise.

## Reference images

- If a reference image is provided: match layout, spacing, typography, and colour exactly. Use placeholder content (`https://placehold.co/WIDTHxHEIGHT`, generic copy). Do **not** improve or extend the design beyond the reference.
- If no reference image: design from scratch with high craft (see **Anti-generic guardrails**).
- Screenshot the implementation, compare against the reference, fix mismatches, re-screenshot. Do **at least two** comparison rounds. Stop only when there are no visible differences left or the user says to stop.

## Local server

- Always review and screenshot over **http://localhost** — never rely on `file://` URLs for visual QA.
- When **`serve.mjs`** exists in the project root, start the dev server with `node serve.mjs` (serves project root at `http://localhost:3000`) in the background before screenshots. If it is already running, do not start a second instance.
- If **`serve.mjs`** is not present yet, use an equivalent static server (e.g. `npx serve .`) on a known port and use that URL for screenshots.
- **Linux paths** — do not use Windows-style paths.

## Screenshot workflow

- When **`screenshot.mjs`** exists in the project root: `node screenshot.mjs http://localhost:3000` (adjust port if needed). Screenshots go to `./screenshots/screenshot-N.png` (auto-incremented). Optional label: `node screenshot.mjs http://localhost:3000 label` → `screenshot-N-label.png`.
- When Puppeteer is available, confirm `which puppeteer` or `node_modules/.bin/` as needed.
- After capturing, **read the PNG** with the image-capable workflow and compare precisely (e.g. “heading is 32px but reference ~24px”, “card gap 16px vs 24px expected”).
- Check: spacing/padding, font size/weight/line-height, colours (exact hex), alignment, border-radius, shadows, image sizing, mobile breakpoints.

## Output defaults

- Single `index.html` with inline styles unless the project type says otherwise.
- Tailwind via CDN: `<script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>`.
- Placeholder images: `https://placehold.co/WIDTHxHEIGHT`.
- **Mobile-first**, responsive.
- **Australian English** in all copy (colour, centre, optimise, etc.).

## Brand assets

- Always check **`brand_assets/`** first.
- If a logo exists, use it. If a palette is defined, use those exact values — do not invent brand colours.
- If a style guide exists, follow it strictly.
- If `brand_assets/` is empty or missing, use high-craft defaults and document colour/font choices for client review.

## Deployment context

- **Target:** Namecheap / cPanel shared hosting.
- Deliver **static files** only unless explicitly agreed otherwise — deployable via FTP (e.g. FileZilla) or cPanel File Manager.
- **Relative asset paths** only — no absolute paths to the domain root.
- Verify behaviour when the site might live in a subdirectory (e.g. `public_html/clientname/`).

## Version control

- Use GitHub; commit logical units with clear messages.
- Do **not** commit `node_modules/`, build artifacts, or screenshot output folders.
- Ensure **`.gitignore`** covers those if missing.

## Anti-generic guardrails

- **Colours:** Do not use the default Tailwind “AI slop” palette as primary (e.g. `indigo-500`, `blue-600`). Use client brand colours or a deliberate custom palette.
- **Shadows:** Avoid flat `shadow-md`. Prefer layered, colour-tinted shadows at low opacity.
- **Typography:** Do not use one font for both headings and body. Pair display/serif with a clean sans. Tight tracking (`-0.03em`) on large headings; generous body line-height (`1.7`).
- **Gradients:** Layer multiple radial gradients; add grain/texture (e.g. SVG noise) for depth where appropriate.
- **Animations:** Only animate `transform` and `opacity`. Never `transition-all`. Prefer spring-style easing.
- **Interactive states:** Every clickable element needs **hover**, **focus-visible**, and **active** states.
- **Images:** Consider gradient overlay (`bg-gradient-to-t from-black/60`) and colour treatment (`mix-blend-multiply`) where it fits the design.
- **Spacing:** Use intentional spacing tokens — not random Tailwind steps.
- **Depth:** Surfaces should read as a system (base → elevated → floating), not one flat plane.

## Hard rules

- Do not add sections, features, or content not in the reference when matching a reference.
- Do not “improve” a reference design — **match** it.
- Do not stop after one screenshot pass when a reference exists.
- Do not use `transition-all`.
- Do not use default Tailwind blue/indigo as the primary brand colour.
- Do not use Windows-style paths.
- Do not use absolute asset paths.
- Australian English in all generated copy.
